org.teatrove.trove.file
Interface TxFileBuffer

All Superinterfaces:
FileBuffer
All Known Implementing Classes:
NonTxFileBuffer, TaggedTxFileBuffer
public interface TxFileBuffer
extends FileBuffer

TxFileBuffer supports transactions.

Author:
Brian S O'Neill

Method Detail

isRollbackSupported

boolean isRollbackSupported()
It is not required for TxFileBuffer implementations to support rollback. If rollback isn't supported, an UnsupportedOperationException is thrown when calling rollback.

isClean

boolean isClean()
                throws IOException
Returns true if this TxFileBuffer is in a known clean state. If false is returned, the file may be corrupt. Exactly how a TxFileBuffer gets in a dirty state depends on the implementaion. In general, isClean should be called before any data is written to a re-opened file.

Throws:
IOException

begin

void begin()
           throws IOException
Begins a transaction. Transactions may be nested, and each call to begin must be matched by a call to commit or rollback.

Throws:
IOException

commit

boolean commit()
               throws IOException
Commits any changes to the file since the last transaction began, but does not necessarily force those changes to disk. If no transaction is in progress, false is returned.

Returns:
true if and only if a transaction was is progress and has been commited.
Throws:
IOException

rollback

boolean rollback()
                 throws IOException,
                        UnsupportedOperationException
Undos all changes made to the file since the last transaction began, but does not necessarily force those changes to disk. If no transaction is in progress, false is returned. If this TxFileBuffer doesn't support rollback, an UnsupportedOperationException is thrown.

Returns:
true if and only if a transaction was is progress and has been rolled back.
Throws:
IOException
UnsupportedOperationException

force

boolean force()
              throws IOException
Forces unwritten data to the physical disk, but does not commit or rollback any transactions.

Specified by:
force in interface FileBuffer
Returns:
false if partially forced.
Throws:
IOException

close

void close()
           throws IOException
Immediately closes the file, with any current transactions left open. This is equivalent to calling close(0).

Specified by:
close in interface FileBuffer
Throws:
IOException

close

void close(long timeout)
           throws IOException
Waits for all transactions to commit or rollback before closing file. A timeout must be specified for the wait. If the value is -1, the timeout is infinite.

Parameters:
timeout - maximum milliseconds to wait to close
Throws:
IOException
